text.section:
The Governor may remove a member of the board for any of the following reasons:
Refusal or inability of a board member to perform his duties as a member of the board in an efficient, responsible and professional manner;
Misuse of the office by a member of the board to obtain personal, pecuniary, or material gain or advantage for himself or another;
Willful violation of any provision of KRS Chapter 315 or any rule or regulation promulgated thereunder.
